The paper deals with a data structure for the planar point location problem, which is a fundamental problem in computational geometry. Therefore, cs.CG (Computational Geometry) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also presents a fully-dynamic data structure, which involves updating the structure as well as querying it, so cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is also a likely sub-category. The external memory model is used, which involves accessing data from disk, so cs.DB (Databases) is another possible sub-category. The paper also involves analyzing the time complexity of the data structure, which falls under cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing). Finally, the paper presents an almost-optimal query cost, which involves analyzing the efficiency of the algorithm, so cs.AL (Algorithms) is another possible sub-category.
